classes.name: SwServiceArg
classes.note: Specifies the properties of a data object exchanged during the call of an SwService, e.g. an argument or a return value. The SwServiceArg can also be used in the argument list of a C-macro. For this purpose the category shall be set to "MACRO". A reference to implementationDataType can optional be added if the actual argument has an implementationDataType.

direction.note: Specifies the direction of the data transfer. The direction indicate the direction of the actual information that is by the caller and/or the callee, not the formal arguments in C. is optional for backwards compatibility example, if a pointer is used to pass a for the expected result, the direction "out". If a pointer is used to pass a memory content to be read by the callee, its direction "in".

swArraysize.note: This turns the argument of the service to an array.

swDataDef.note: Data properties of this SwServiceArg. atpSplitable
